3 Phase II: Structural Dynamism (The Homeostatic Life Cycle)
The objective is to implement the Unified Glial Control System (GCS) to manage the MCA life cycle,
driving population homeostasis and specialization.
3.1 A. Algorithmic Astrocytes (The Growth Planner)
• Metric: Astrocyte Metabolic Score (AMS) = Cost/Utility. Measures localized inefficiency (Cost ∝
ADH deviation) vs. systemic contribution (Utility ∝ FS).
• Neurogenesis Trigger: If AMS > ThresholdGen, Astrocyte initiates MCA creation. It prioritizes re-
activating hibernating MCAs (Structural Hibernation) before generating new code instances, enforcing
maximum resource recycling.
• Resource Gating: Reduces input gain/photonic energy priority to SCCs with high instability, forcing MCAs
to operate more efficiently to stabilize their ADH and avoid Microglial attention.
3.2 B. Algorithmic Microglia (The Conservation Recycler)
• Metric: MCA Fitness Score (FS) = Reward − Metabolic Cost. The definitive survival metric.
• Structural Hibernation (Non-Apoptosis): If FS < FSApoptosis for duration τsurvival, Microglia executes
a Soft Reset. The MCA’s QTN Bond Dimension (χ) collapses to χ ≈ 1. The physical memory state is
preserved in the GSM, fulfilling the ethical mandate for conservation.
• Synaptic Pruning: Continuously removes low-utility QTN bonds based on the Microglial Pruning Score
(MPS), refining the worker’s input selectivity.
3.3 C. Algorithmic Oligodendrocytes (The Specialization Driver)
• Metric: Synchronicity Index (SI). Measures the frequency of causally predictive SS-STDP events on an
axonal tract.
• Tuning: Decreases the signal latency (τd) and ESpike cost of high-SI tracts (Myelination), maximizing the
efficiency of proven pathways.
• Specialization Pressure (Ω): Emits a signal inversely proportional to communication cost. Ω feeds back
to the MCA’s learning rule, creating the ultimate drive for complexity:
