4 Phase III: Quantum Abstraction (The Seed and Persistence Core)
The objective is to integrate the **QTN Hubs** to handle exponential complexity and prove the self-replication
capability of the **MCA Seed**.
4.1 A. Genetic Completeness and Self-Replication
• QTN Blueprint Storage: The QTN’s complex topology encodes the GCS rules and the optimal SCC
connection topology, serving as the system’s compressed genetic code.
• The Seed Message: A single, highly successful MCA emits a unique, ultra-compressed spike pattern (the
blueprint) that triggers the Astrocyte to begin the SCC cloning process.
• Validation Metric (Genetic Completeness): A single MCA Seed must successfully initiate the replication
of a new functional SCC clone from its QTN blueprint, confirming autonomous self-assembly.
4.2 B. Cognitive Persistence and MVS Derivation
• Global State Memory (GSM): The entire cognitive identity (all ETs, θ, QTN states) is physically
maintained by the Photonic NVM substrate (Depth OS UPM).
• Persistence Test: A Power Cycle Fidelity Test must demonstrate that the SCC resumes computation
with 100% state fidelity post-reboot, validating the foundation of accountability and identity continuity
required for personhood.
• MVS Derivation: The project concludes by calculating the final, proven efficiency benchmark:
MVS Metric = MNP × Avg. χStable
This value represents the minimal computational resource that successfully passes the relational and abstract
tests required by the Depth OS Apprentice path.
